# Beehiiv Review: The Newsletter Platform Built for Growth

## What Is Beehiiv?

[Beehiiv](https://www.beehiiv.com) is a newsletter platform designed from the ground up for creators, writers, and small businesses who want to build an audience and turn it into revenue. Unlike traditional email marketing tools that treat newsletters as a secondary feature, Beehiiv treats newsletters as the core product. It combines email publishing, website hosting, subscriber analytics, and monetization tools in a single dashboard. We use Beehiiv for the WorkMultiple newsletter, and we appreciate how it prioritizes the growth-to-monetization workflow that most independent creators actually need.

## Who Should Use Beehiiv?

Beehiiv works best for specific use cases:

**Independent Writers and Journalists**: If you're building a subscriber-owned publication and want to write, send, and earn money without worrying about infrastructure, Beehiiv handles all of that for you.

**Content Creators and Thought Leaders**: Professionals who want to build direct relationships with their audience and potentially monetize through paid tiers or ads will find Beehiiv's feature set purpose-built for this.

**Side Hustlers and Entrepreneurs**: If you're starting a newsletter as a side business or to generate supplemental income, Beehiiv's [referral program](https://www.beehiiv.com/features/referral-program), [ad network](https://www.beehiiv.com/ad-network), and paid subscription tools are more mature than what you'll find in entry-level competitors.

**Small Brands and Newsletters**: Beehiiv works for businesses running regular newsletters, but it's not designed for ecommerce companies that need SMS, multi-channel campaigns, or heavy automation workflows. ([Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com) is better for that use case.)

**Podcasters and Newsletter Bundles**: Beehiiv integrates with audio and lets you build multi-content-type publications in one place.

## [Key Features](https://www.beehiiv.com/features)

### Email Editor and Design

Beehiiv's email editor is drag-and-drop and mobile-optimized, which is good for quickly creating newsletters. You get a library of templates, and the interface is intuitive enough that non-designers can produce clean-looking emails. However, the template library is smaller than Mailchimp's, and if you need highly custom email designs, you'll hit limitations. One technical limitation: emails can bump against Beehiiv's 102kb file size limit, which means some beautifully designed newsletters can clip mid-content if they're too graphically heavy.

### Website Builder and Blog

One of Beehiiv's standout features is the integrated website builder. You can turn your newsletter into a full publication website with archived posts, subscriber-only content, and landing pages. Posts automatically get published to both your website and sent to subscribers' inboxes. The website builder is AI-powered (on paid plans) and includes drag-and-drop sections, testimonial blocks, featured post galleries, and custom HTML support. This eliminates the need for separate tools like [Substack](https://substack.com) or [Ghost](https://ghost.org) if you don't need extreme customization.

### Landing Pages and Sign-up Forms

Beehiiv includes custom landing pages (available on Scale plan and above) that let you build sign-up pages without leaving the platform. You can track conversions from your email back to your landing page with built-in analytics. The sign-up form builder is simple and works with [Webflow](https://webflow.com) (though only via iframe), but tight integration is limited to Beehiiv's own website builder.

### Analytics and Growth Insights

The analytics dashboard shows subscriber origin (social, blog, referral, direct), growth trends, engagement metrics, and performance per email send. You can see which posts drive subscriber acquisition and which emails generate the most opens and clicks. This level of visibility is valuable for optimizing your growth strategy. However, Beehiiv's subscriber tracking only shows medium source (e.g., "social") and doesn't track specific articles that drove signups, which can be a limitation for content-heavy newsletters.

### Referral Program

Beehiiv's referral program is built in and can be spun up in a few clicks. Each subscriber gets a unique referral link, and you set rewards for milestones (e.g., "refer 5 friends, get a free paid month"). The system automatically tracks referrals, notifies subscribers of progress, and distributes rewards. This is a growth tool that many competitors require third-party integrations to offer.

### Monetization Tools

Beehiiv offers three primary revenue streams:

**Paid Subscriptions**: You can create paid tiers with options like monthly, annual, or "pay what you want" pricing. Beehiiv takes 0% of subscription revenue, which is significantly better than [Substack](https://substack.com)'s 10% cut. You can gate content behind paywalls and offer multiple premium tiers.

**Ad Network**: The [Beehiiv Ad Network](https://www.beehiiv.com/ad-network) connects your newsletter with advertisers. Every Sunday, you receive ad opportunities with estimated payouts. Payment models include CPM (cost per thousand opens) and CPC (cost per click). The minimum subscriber count to start earning ads varies, but the Scale plan includes a monetization guarantee, meaning you're guaranteed at least some ad placements. Earnings from ads typically start low (a few cents per thousand opens) but scale with your subscriber count and engagement rates.

**Boosts and Recommendations**: You can recommend products or services to your audience and earn a commission if you set up affiliate links. Beehiiv calls this "Boosts," and it integrates directly into your newsletter sending flow.

The combination of these three tools means a 5,000-subscriber newsletter could generate revenue from ads alone, even without paid subscriptions. This is a major differentiator from Mailchimp and a key reason creators choose Beehiiv.

### Email Automation

Beehiiv supports automations like welcome sequences, post notifications, and conditional sends. However, automation capabilities are limited compared to [ActiveCampaign](https://www.activecampaign.com) or [Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com). For example, automations are capped at 30 days, and you can't segment subscribers by tags (Beehiiv only distinguishes paid vs. unpaid). If you need complex multi-step automation workflows with advanced segmentation, this is a weakness.

### Integrations

Beehiiv integrates with [Zapier](https://zapier.com) and [Make](https://www.make.com) for automation workflows. Check out our detailed comparison of [Zapier vs Make](/blog/zapier-vs-make) to see which automation platform works best with Beehiiv. Beehiiv also connects with [Shopify](https://www.shopify.com), [Stripe](https://stripe.com), and [Substack](https://substack.com). You can pull data into other tools via Zapier if the native integration isn't available. However, API documentation is limited compared to larger platforms, and custom integrations may require workarounds.

## [Pricing](https://www.beehiiv.com/pricing) Breakdown

Beehiiv uses a subscriber-based pricing model with four main tiers:

### Launch (Free)

Up to 2,500 subscribers, unlimited email sends. No monetization features. No email automations. No paid subscriptions or ads. No website builder or landing pages. No referral program. Best for: testing the platform or very small hobby newsletters.

### Scale ($49/month)

Up to 100,000 subscribers (then upgrade to Enterprise). Includes email automations, paid subscriptions at 0% platform fee, access to the ad network with monetization guarantee, website and landing page builder, referral program, Zapier integrations, priority support, and surveys. Pricing scales: $49 for 1,001-5,000 subscribers, and increases incrementally as you grow. Annual billing saves 20%.

### Max ($109/month)

Everything in Scale, plus priority support, NewsletterXP course access, Beehiiv branding removal, and early access to new features. Same subscriber limits as Scale; pricing scales incrementally. Annual billing saves 20%.

### Enterprise (Custom)

For newsletters with 100,000+ subscribers. Custom pricing and dedicated support.

**Hidden Costs and Considerations**:

- No price jump for growing within a tier (pricing scales smoothly as you add subscribers)
- Annual discount (20% off): $40/month for Scale, $87/month for Max if paid yearly
- Payment processor fees (Stripe) apply when processing paid subscriptions
- No setup fees or cancellation penalties

For most creators, the Scale plan at $49/month is the sweet spot. The Max plan is only worth it if you need priority support or want the course. The free tier is genuinely useful for getting started but severely limits your growth potential.

## Strengths

**Growth-First Design**: Every feature is optimized for growth. The referral program, analytics, and recommendation tools are built in, not bolted on. Most creators using Beehiiv see faster subscriber growth than they did with Mailchimp or Mailerlite.

**Monetization Integration**: Three revenue streams (ads, subscriptions, boosts) in one platform, with 0% platform fees on subscriptions. This is substantially better than Substack (which takes 10%) and Mailchimp (which doesn't offer integrated monetization at all).

**Ease of Use**: The interface is clean and intuitive. You don't need design or coding skills to create professional newsletters and build a website. Onboarding is smooth, and documentation is solid.

**No Lock-in**: You own your subscriber list. Exports are easy. You can migrate away at any time without penalty. This contrasts with some platforms that make switching difficult.

**Responsive Support**: Users consistently praise Beehiiv's support team for responsiveness via email, Slack, and social channels. For a creator tool at this price point, the support quality is exceptional.

**Feature Velocity**: Beehiiv releases new features regularly (landing pages, AI website builder, custom domains). The product roadmap is responsive to user feedback.

**Integrated Ecosystem**: Email, website, landing pages, analytics, and monetization all live in one dashboard. You don't need to duct-tape five different tools together.

## Weaknesses

**Limited Automation and Segmentation**: You can't segment by custom tags or fields. Automations are capped at 30 days. If you need sophisticated workflows (e.g., "if subscriber clicked link A but not link B in the last 14 days, send sequence X"), you'll hit the ceiling quickly.

**Email Design Limits**: The template library is smaller than competitors. Highly custom HTML emails can run into the 102kb file size limit and clip in rendering. This is a minor issue for text-heavy newsletters but a real problem for design-heavy ones.

**Pricing Jump for Small Creators**: There's no middle ground between free (2,500 subscribers) and $49/month. If you're at 3,000 subscribers and generating minimal revenue, the jump feels steep. A $19/month tier would bridge this gap.

**Limited Contact Management**: No custom fields, tags, or lists. You can only distinguish paid from unpaid subscribers. This makes segmentation beyond "paid vs. free" impossible without workarounds.

**Occasional Downtime and Bugs**: Several users report bugs, tablet rendering issues, and occasional downtime. The Stripe integration has had reported errors. The platform is still maturing, and reliability issues are occasional but noteworthy.

**Limited Design Flexibility**: While the template library is improving, you can't upload custom themes or access a third-party theme marketplace like WordPress offers. You're limited to what Beehiiv provides.

**Support for Urgent Issues**: While general support is responsive, some users report slow responses for urgent, business-critical issues. The support tier is primarily email-based unless you're on the Max plan with priority support.

## Beehiiv vs. Alternatives

For a comprehensive comparison of email platforms, see our full breakdown of [Beehiiv vs Kit vs Mailchimp](/blog/beehiiv-vs-kit-vs-mailchimp) to help you choose the right platform for your needs.

### Beehiiv vs. Mailchimp

[Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com) is an email marketing platform built for ecommerce and multi-channel campaigns. Beehiiv is a newsletter platform built for audience-first creators. Mailchimp has superior automation and segmentation but lacks built-in monetization and treats newsletters as a secondary feature. Mailchimp's free tier is generous (up to 500 contacts), but pricing scales to $110+/month as you grow. Mailchimp's template library is larger, but the interface is less intuitive. For newsletters and creator monetization, Beehiiv wins. For small ecommerce brands running campaigns, Mailchimp wins.

### Beehiiv vs. Substack

[Substack](https://substack.com) is free to start and takes 10% of subscription revenue. Beehiiv charges $49/month but takes 0% of subscription revenue. For newsletters under 500 subscribers, Substack is cheaper. For newsletters generating revenue (say, 1,000+ subscribers with paid tiers), Beehiiv's 0% cut means higher takehome earnings. Substack excels at community building and discussion threads; Beehiiv excels at monetization and website integration. Substack has a built-in discovery network; Beehiiv doesn't. Substack is simpler; Beehiiv is more powerful.

### Beehiiv vs. ConvertKit (Kit)

[ConvertKit](https://kit.com) recently rebranded to Kit and positioned itself as an all-in-one creator platform. Kit offers similar features (email, landing pages, monetization) but has a different pricing model and is more focused on digital products (courses, ebooks). Beehiiv's email editor is more advanced. Kit's product integrations are stronger if you're selling courses. For pure newsletters, Beehiiv is slightly more polished. For creators with multi-product offerings, Kit might be better.

### Beehiiv vs. Ghost

[Ghost](https://ghost.org) is an open-source CMS and newsletter platform. If you want full control and don't mind technical setup, Ghost is powerful. Beehiiv is cloud-hosted and requires zero technical knowledge. Ghost is better if you need SEO control and membership management; Beehiiv is better if you want simplicity and built-in growth tools.

## Frequently Asked Questions

### How much money can you make with Beehiiv ads?

Earnings vary widely based on your subscriber count and engagement. A 5,000-subscriber newsletter with strong opens (40%+) might earn $100-$500/month from ads. A 50,000-subscriber newsletter could earn $2,000-$10,000+/month. Most creators combine ads with paid subscriptions to reach meaningful revenue. The Beehiiv Ad Network guarantees placements on the Scale plan, but rates start low and scale up as your reputation grows.

### Is Beehiiv better than Substack?

It depends on your goals. If you want simplicity and don't need monetization, Substack is free and sufficient. If you want to monetize aggressively or build a custom website, Beehiiv is better. Substack's 10% cut of subscriptions adds up; at $1,000/month in subscription revenue, you lose $100 to Substack. Beehiiv's $49/month fee plus 0% cut becomes the better deal at scale.

### Can you migrate from Substack to Beehiiv?

Yes. Beehiiv provides import tools and migration guides. Your subscriber list exports easily, and you can set up redirects to avoid losing readers. Migration is straightforward but requires manual setup for some elements (custom branding, integrations).

### Does Beehiiv work for B2B newsletters?

Yes. B2B newsletters benefit from Beehiiv's analytics, landing pages, and segmentation tools. However, Beehiiv lacks advanced automations and custom fields that some B2B marketers need. For complex B2B workflows, [Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com) or [ActiveCampaign](https://www.activecampaign.com) might be more suitable.

### What's included in the free plan?

2,500 subscribers, unlimited email sends, basic templates, analytics, and sign-up forms. No automations, no monetization features, no website builder, no landing pages. The free plan is a true trial; after 2,500 subscribers, you must upgrade.

### Does Beehiiv have an API?

Yes, but documentation is limited. [Zapier](https://zapier.com) and [Make](https://www.make.com) integrations cover most use cases. Custom API integrations are possible but less documented than [Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com) or [ActiveCampaign](https://www.activecampaign.com).

## Verdict

Beehiiv is the best newsletter platform for creators and independent writers who want to grow an audience and monetize it. The combination of intuitive design, built-in growth tools, zero platform fees on subscriptions, and an integrated ad network make it unmatched for this use case. The free tier lets you start with no financial commitment, and the $49/month Scale plan is priced fairly.

The main trade-offs are automation limitations and occasional stability issues. If you need complex email sequences or have been burned by platform reliability, these weaknesses matter. But for 90% of creators, Beehiiv's trade-off (simpler, more focused, faster growth) is the right one.

If you're coming from [Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com) because your needs have changed from marketing campaigns to building a publication, Beehiiv is a clear upgrade. If you're on [Substack](https://substack.com) and generating real revenue, switching to Beehiiv saves you 10% on every dollar earned. If you're just starting and want a simple, powerful platform to build an audience, Beehiiv is the fastest path.

The only scenario where we'd recommend alternatives: if you need advanced automation and segmentation (pick [Mailchimp](https://mailchimp.com)), if you want true open-source control (pick [Ghost](https://ghost.org)), or if you want rock-bottom entry costs with community features (pick [Substack](https://substack.com)). Otherwise, Beehiiv earns its reputation as the growth-focused newsletter platform for creators.

